docs {
  ## Add Attachments to Stock Out Comment
  อัปโหลดไฟล์แนบหลายไฟล์เข้ากับคอมเมนต์ที่มีอยู่แล้วใน request เดียว

  Uploads one or more file attachments to an existing stock-out comment in a single multipart request.

  ### Path Parameters
  | Name | Type | Description |
  |------|------|-------------|
  | `bu_code` | string | Business unit code |
  | `id` | string (UUID) | Comment ID |

  ### Query Parameters
  | Name | Type | Required | Default | Description |
  |------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
  | `version` | string | No | latest | API version |

  ### Headers
  | Name | Required | Description |
  |------|----------|-------------|
  | `Authorization` | Yes | `Bearer {{access_token}}` |
  | `x-app-id` | Yes | `{{x_app_id}}` |

  ### Permissions
  - **Permission key**: `inventory_management.stock_out:update`
  - **Roles**: Purchase

  ### Body (multipart/form-data)
  | Field | Type | Required | Description |
  |-------|------|----------|-------------|
  | `files` | binary (repeatable) | Yes | File attachments (1–10 files) |

  **File constraints**: max 10 files, max 10 MB each; allowed: image/jpeg, image/png, image/webp, image/gif, application/pdf

  ### Gateway behavior
  1. Upload all files to S3 in parallel via `file.upload`
  2. If any upload fails — rollback (delete successfully uploaded files from S3) and respond 502
  3. Send `{ id, attachments: [...] }` to business service via `stock-out-comment.add-attachment`
  4. If business returns error — rollback and delete uploaded files from S3

  ### Sample Response
  ```json
  {
    "data": {
      "id": "019638a6-2a00-7c4f-8e46-9b7a52c80c4d",
      "attachments": [
        {
          "fileName": "photo.jpg",
          "fileToken": "BU001/019638a6-2a00-7c4f-8e46-9b7a52c80c4d",
          "fileUrl": "",
          "contentType": "image/jpeg",
          "size": 204800
        }
      ]
    },
    "paginate": null,
    "status": 200,
    "success": true,
    "message": "Success",
    "timestamp": "2026-04-29T08:30:00.000Z"
  }
  ```

  > Note: `fileUrl` ใน response จะว่าง — frontend ต้องเรียก `GET /api/{bu_code}/documents/presigned-url/{fileToken}` เพื่อแสดงไฟล์

  ### Error Responses
  | Status | When |
  |--------|------|
  | 400 | No files provided |
  | 401 | Missing or invalid bearer token |
  | 403 | User lacks `inventory_management.stock_out:update` permission |
  | 404 | Comment not found |
  | 502 | S3 upload failed |

  > Service-layer errors propagate via TCP; see micro-business for full list.
}
